{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"89a41108-024f-440f-b594-45d097c355af","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# API with Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg\n\n# API with Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API style (default in .NET 6+)\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nFor JWT Bearer token auth without Azure AD, start with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5dec2fb1-ad2f-4172-9a99-730d79a829bd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET development question. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge, since this doesn't require exploring any codebase.","outputTokens":318,"requestId":"9C10:1ED388:1CC0123:2037E17:6A07BFBE"},"id":"cbbddd2f-f4fe-4bc1-a02b-6619f3148cd0","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:52:24.275Z","parentId":"2d42df4e-44da-4681-a579-aa63d1b4771d"}
